19
00:00:18,397 --> 00:00:19,440
<i>Stranded!</i>

20
00:00:19,482 --> 00:00:21,317
<i>On a secret mission for the Republic,</i>

21
00:00:21,442 --> 00:00:24,320
<i>Colonel Gascon
and his intrepid droid squad</i>

22
00:00:24,445 --> 00:00:27,990
<i>successfully steal an encryption module
from a Separatist ship.</i>

23
00:00:28,324 --> 00:00:32,453
<i>During their escape, our heroes crash
on the Outer Rim planet of Abafar</i>

24
00:00:33,079 --> 00:00:37,083
<i>and find themselves stranded
in the strange wasteland called The Void.</i>

25
00:00:37,625 --> 00:00:41,963
<i>Now, after surviving against all odds,
our heroes must find a way home</i>

26
00:00:42,088 --> 00:00:45,800
<i>and deliver the encryption module
to crack the Separatist code</i>

27
00:00:45,925 --> 00:00:47,635
<i>and stop an enemy attack.</i>

28
00:00:50,137 --> 00:00:54,141
I have never been to Tatooine,
but if this place reminds you of it, Artoo,

29
00:00:54,267 --> 00:00:56,143
remind me never to go there.

30
00:01:01,816 --> 00:01:05,319
Don't be absurd, Qutee.
These people aren't dangerous.

31
00:01:15,997 --> 00:01:20,501
Most of these people are probably hiding
from someone or something.

32
00:01:21,043 --> 00:01:24,213
That's the way it is
on these Outer Rim armpits.

33
00:01:24,338 --> 00:01:25,464
Nobody's here by choice.

34
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:27,508
Which goes double for me!

35
00:01:27,675 --> 00:01:31,512
I hope you have a plan
to get us off this armpit, Colonel.

36
00:01:31,846 --> 00:01:33,681
Of course I do, Corporal.

37
00:01:34,181 --> 00:01:37,560
All we need is a communications uplink
and some fuel.

38
00:01:39,353 --> 00:01:41,564
Thank you for the reminder, Ceefor,

39
00:01:41,689 --> 00:01:44,692
but I'm well aware
our shuttle's lost in the Void.

40
00:01:44,734 --> 00:01:47,028
I'm talking about fuel for me!

41
00:01:47,570 --> 00:01:50,573
You droids can putter along
on battery power,

42
00:01:50,698 --> 00:01:52,533
but I need food to survive.

43
00:01:53,409 --> 00:01:55,494
My power cells are running low, too.

44
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:57,830
And an oil bath would be nice.

45
00:01:58,080 --> 00:02:01,167
All this dust is wreaking havoc
on my joints.

46
00:02:02,835 --> 00:02:05,838
Forget it, Beezee.
We're not on vacation here.

47
00:02:06,047 --> 00:02:08,549
Artoo, is the encryption module safe?

48
00:02:10,885 --> 00:02:15,348
Nothing short of death or dismemberment
will stop Colonel Meebur Gascon

49
00:02:15,389 --> 00:02:18,100
from delivering that module to Coruscant.

50
00:02:22,730 --> 00:02:24,190
Well, I'll be.

51
00:02:24,774 --> 00:02:27,443
A diner! A place of eating !

52
00:02:27,777 --> 00:02:29,028
I'm saved!

53
00:02:29,195 --> 00:02:31,906
Artoo! You and the other mechs
scout the perimeter,

54
00:02:32,031 --> 00:02:35,034
find out if there are
any unfriendlies around.

55
00:02:35,242 --> 00:02:39,747
Corporal, you and I will refuel
in this fine establishment.

56
00:02:55,388 --> 00:02:56,555
Good day.

57
00:03:00,226 --> 00:03:04,438
I am Colonel Gascon
of the Grand Army of the Republic,

58
00:03:04,939 --> 00:03:07,400
and I am here on very important business.

59
00:03:14,156 --> 00:03:15,616
I don't have much time,

60
00:03:15,658 --> 00:03:18,786
so if you'll be so kind
as to fix me your daily special

61
00:03:18,828 --> 00:03:21,831
-and let my droid recharge...
-No droids!

62
00:03:24,625 --> 00:03:25,793
Fine.

63
00:03:26,961 --> 00:03:28,838
Wait for me outside, Corporal.

64
00:03:29,630 --> 00:03:31,966
We don't serve your type, either!

65
00:03:32,675 --> 00:03:35,344
What type are you referring to?

66
00:03:35,636 --> 00:03:38,222
Conduit worms.

67
00:03:41,809 --> 00:03:44,854
I beg your pardon. I am a Zilkan!

68
00:03:45,229 --> 00:03:49,734
You'll be begging for your life
if you don't beat it!

69
00:03:52,319 --> 00:03:54,321
Beat it.

70
00:03:54,572 --> 00:03:56,323
Uh-oh.

71
00:03:59,243 --> 00:04:01,829
This is an outrage!

72
00:04:01,871 --> 00:04:05,916
That monstrosity will rue the day
he denied me a meal!

73
00:04:06,375 --> 00:04:08,002
I would not push it, Colonel.

74
00:04:08,043 --> 00:04:10,671
That monstrosity might make a meal
out of you.

75
00:04:11,088 --> 00:04:13,716
I don't care. I'm famished!

76
00:04:20,222 --> 00:04:22,266
I think I can help.

77
00:04:34,069 --> 00:04:36,197
Your meal awaits you, sir.

78
00:04:37,573 --> 00:04:41,869
You short-circuiting hydrospanner.
That's no meal!

79
00:04:41,952 --> 00:04:43,746
That is garbage!

80
00:04:43,913 --> 00:04:46,624
What is the difference?
It is edible, is it not?

81
00:04:47,082 --> 00:04:48,876
Ugh !

82
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,069
Oh !

83
00:05:16,237 --> 00:05:17,404
Oh!

84
00:05:17,446 --> 00:05:19,156
Sorry. I didn't see you there.

85
00:05:19,573 --> 00:05:23,619
Look, I can get you some food,
but normally people come in the front door.

86
00:05:24,245 --> 00:05:25,329
It's no problem.

87
00:05:27,414 --> 00:05:30,125
You do know
that you're eating garbage, right?

88
00:05:32,503 --> 00:05:34,255
You're a clone!

89
00:05:34,630 --> 00:05:35,798
Excuse me?

90
00:05:36,090 --> 00:05:37,258
Uh...

91
00:05:38,008 --> 00:05:40,678
I wouldn't know about that.
My name's Gregor.

92
00:05:41,011 --> 00:05:43,013
Uh, wait, what's a clone?

93
00:05:50,187 --> 00:05:52,356
You are a clone!

94
00:05:52,439 --> 00:05:54,024
Are you working undercover?

95
00:05:54,358 --> 00:05:57,152
I don't know what you're talking about.

96
00:05:57,361 --> 00:05:59,738
Listen to me, soldier.
Whatever your assignment is,

97
00:05:59,822 --> 00:06:01,782
it can't be more important than mine.

98
00:06:01,866 --> 00:06:03,492
It is his first real mission.

99
00:06:03,742 --> 00:06:05,160
He is just a map reader.

100
00:06:05,494 --> 00:06:07,621
Don't listen to that ignoramus.

101
00:06:07,705 --> 00:06:11,208
You are a clone
and a soldier in the Republic Army,

102
00:06:11,292 --> 00:06:13,586
and I order you to take me to your ship!

103
00:06:14,086 --> 00:06:16,297
We need to get back
to Coruscant immediately.

104
00:06:17,089 --> 00:06:19,425
Look, friend, I was just trying to help.

105
00:06:19,675 --> 00:06:21,510
I'm sorry if you took it the wrong way.

106
00:06:21,802 --> 00:06:24,680
I do not think that soldier
believes you are a colonel,

107
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:26,307
Colonel.

108
00:06:26,807 --> 00:06:30,102
Gregor! Get back to work!

109
00:06:31,103 --> 00:06:33,772
Excuse me, I gotta go.
I don't want to lose my job.

110
00:06:37,276 --> 00:06:39,528
But I'm still hungry!

111
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:54,919
Well? What's the scouting report?

112
00:06:58,881 --> 00:07:00,799
Separatist droids? Hmm.

113
00:07:00,966 --> 00:07:03,302
Well, that complicates matters.

114
00:07:06,555 --> 00:07:09,600
So, uh, boss,

115
00:07:10,142 --> 00:07:11,936
you know,
I was just wondering...

116
00:07:12,019 --> 00:07:14,647
No, you can't have a raise, Gregor.

117
00:07:15,064 --> 00:07:17,608
Oh, no, no, no, I don't want a raise.

118
00:07:18,275 --> 00:07:21,028
I just wanted to know, what's a clone?

119
00:07:22,071 --> 00:07:26,158
Someone told me I was a clone today.
They insisted.

120
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:28,202
A clone?

121
00:07:28,535 --> 00:07:31,288
Clones fight battles across the galaxy.

122
00:07:31,622 --> 00:07:33,332
They are brave soldiers.

123
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:36,001
Does that sound like you?

124
00:07:36,710 --> 00:07:39,588
You're a dishwasher, Gregor.

125
00:07:39,672 --> 00:07:43,092
Forget about clones or anything like that.

126
00:07:43,217 --> 00:07:47,054
You have good life here, a simple life.

127
00:07:47,346 --> 00:07:49,932
More than you had when Borkus found you.

128
00:07:50,182 --> 00:07:53,352
I know, sir, and I appreciate
everything that you've done, believe me.

129
00:07:53,602 --> 00:07:57,731
But I thought maybe you could...
Could you tell me, how did I get here?

130
00:07:58,232 --> 00:07:59,358
Where did you find me?

131
00:07:59,525 --> 00:08:01,944
Enough questions! Go home. Sleep!

132
00:08:02,653 --> 00:08:04,363
Come back tomorrow, do your job.

133
00:08:05,906 --> 00:08:09,743
And I don't ever want to hear
that word "clone" again. Understand?

134
00:08:20,796 --> 00:08:25,259
Colonel, I cannot help noticing
that we are already on our third plan.

135
00:08:26,093 --> 00:08:30,514
Smart battle strategy requires
flexibility and improvisation,

136
00:08:30,931 --> 00:08:32,975
something droids are not known for.

137
00:08:35,310 --> 00:08:38,814
Artoo is right.
Droids are not known for being flexible

138
00:08:38,981 --> 00:08:41,734
because we are programmed
to be right the first time.

139
00:08:42,067 --> 00:08:44,069
Well, answer me this, Corporal.

140
00:08:44,153 --> 00:08:46,947
If the Jedi Council thought
one of you droids

141
00:08:47,031 --> 00:08:49,283
were better prepared to lead this mission,

142
00:08:49,408 --> 00:08:51,535
then why did they put me in charge?

143
00:08:52,119 --> 00:08:54,872
'Cause you're the only one
who could fit inside Beezee.

144
00:08:57,082 --> 00:09:00,669
No, it is because
my power of deduction told me

145
00:09:00,753 --> 00:09:03,714
that if there are Separatist droids
on Abafar,

146
00:09:03,964 --> 00:09:06,633
then there must be a landing zone nearby,

147
00:09:06,717 --> 00:09:09,762
where there will be, no doubt,
a shuttle to take us home.

148
00:09:10,721 --> 00:09:14,183
That, Corporal, is why I am in charge.

149
00:09:17,478 --> 00:09:20,189
Now, we are going to waltz down there,

150
00:09:20,272 --> 00:09:23,192
undetected, just like we did
on the dreadnought,

151
00:09:23,275 --> 00:09:26,445
and commandeer that shuttle
without incident.

152
00:09:29,031 --> 00:09:30,324
The mechs have a point, Colonel.

153
00:09:30,407 --> 00:09:32,117
After what we did on the dreadnought,

154
00:09:32,201 --> 00:09:35,204
those battle droids probably have
our identities scanned.

155
00:09:35,287 --> 00:09:38,165
We will have to fight our way
onto the shuttle this time.

156
00:09:38,248 --> 00:09:40,459
Mmm, you droids may have a point.

157
00:09:40,709 --> 00:09:45,089
But there's no way in Malachor
that I'm gonna lead this pitiful squad

158
00:09:45,172 --> 00:09:47,633
on an assault of that landing zone.

159
00:09:47,966 --> 00:09:49,301
What is the plan now, Colonel?

160
00:09:49,676 --> 00:09:53,305
We're going to wait
until our clone gets off work,

161
00:09:53,388 --> 00:09:57,392
then enlist his help,
whether he wants to or not.

162
00:10:50,445 --> 00:10:52,948
<i>- Captain Rex, reporting for duty.</i>
- What?

163
00:10:59,329 --> 00:11:00,455
I...

164
00:11:01,290 --> 00:11:03,458
I don't understand. That's...

165
00:11:04,376 --> 00:11:07,087
- Me?
- No, that's Captain Rex.

166
00:11:07,421 --> 00:11:11,800
He's a clone in the Republic Army,
just like you, Gregor.

167
00:11:12,384 --> 00:11:14,428
I can't believe it.

168
00:11:15,888 --> 00:11:17,222
Okay, slow down, slow down.

169
00:11:17,306 --> 00:11:21,643
So you're telling me
that there are more of these clones.

170
00:11:21,977 --> 00:11:24,104
Millions. A whole army's worth.

171
00:11:24,938 --> 00:11:26,064
Aha.

172
00:11:26,732 --> 00:11:31,028
-And they all look exactly like me?
-No.

173
00:11:31,278 --> 00:11:36,283
Those clones are warriors, professional
soldiers created by the Republic,

174
00:11:36,450 --> 00:11:39,828
trained to fight, and die if necessary,

175
00:11:39,912 --> 00:11:41,622
in our war against the Separatists.

176
00:11:42,206 --> 00:11:46,919
They're not dishwashers
living in some vermin-infested hovel.

177
00:11:49,004 --> 00:11:51,465
Look, I'm lucky to live in this place.

178
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:54,760
Mr. Borkus says
my salary doesn't even cover the rent,

179
00:11:54,843 --> 00:11:58,180
-so he pays the difference for me.
-Don't you get it, Gregor?

180
00:11:58,555 --> 00:12:02,142
You're his slave!
We need to figure out who you really are,

181
00:12:02,226 --> 00:12:03,560
how you got here.

182
00:12:04,186 --> 00:12:06,063
Are you sure
you don't remember anything?

183
00:12:06,980 --> 00:12:09,775
Well, all I remember

184
00:12:10,275 --> 00:12:12,945
is waking up on a transport.

185
00:12:13,028 --> 00:12:16,198
Somehow we crashed on Abafar, and...

186
00:12:16,281 --> 00:12:19,618
Well, Mr. Borkus says I have amnesia.

187
00:12:19,826 --> 00:12:24,122
Hmm. Every clone has an identifying code
on their wrist.

188
00:12:24,206 --> 00:12:26,625
Your military records will be
in the database.

189
00:12:27,042 --> 00:12:28,377
Scan him, Artoo.

190
00:12:35,968 --> 00:12:37,219
Impressive.

191
00:12:37,719 --> 00:12:43,100
Gregor, your designation is CC5576-39.

192
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:46,895
You were a captain
and part of an elite squad.

193
00:12:47,938 --> 00:12:49,439
A clone commando.

194
00:12:52,150 --> 00:12:54,820
Your file says you were reported
missing in action

195
00:12:54,903 --> 00:12:58,115
during the Battle of Sarrish.

196
00:12:59,574 --> 00:13:00,784
Sarrish?

197
00:13:02,077 --> 00:13:03,412
Sarrish.

198
00:13:04,162 --> 00:13:05,414
Wait.

199
00:13:06,039 --> 00:13:08,041
What was the Battle of Sarrish?

200
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:12,045
It was one of the Republic's
most devastating losses.

201
00:13:12,129 --> 00:13:13,797
Sarrish.

202
00:13:14,673 --> 00:13:17,509
Yes. Yes, I remember now.

203
00:13:18,427 --> 00:13:20,137
So many soldiers were dying.

204
00:13:20,762 --> 00:13:23,974
Do you remember
how you escaped Sarrish?

205
00:13:25,809 --> 00:13:30,105
No. I just remember
seeing all those bodies.

206
00:13:31,523 --> 00:13:32,566
Bodies everywhere.

207
00:13:33,734 --> 00:13:35,819
I knew I had to get help,

208
00:13:35,902 --> 00:13:38,989
but that's where the memory stops.

209
00:13:39,197 --> 00:13:43,160
Well, soldier, there's nothing you can do
about that battle now,

210
00:13:43,660 --> 00:13:45,412
but you can help us.

211
00:13:45,871 --> 00:13:47,873
Our mission depends on it.

212
00:13:55,505 --> 00:13:59,468
Colonel, Gregor said to give him
five minutes, but it has been six.

213
00:14:00,135 --> 00:14:02,095
What if he does not accept
your offer to join us?

214
00:14:02,387 --> 00:14:06,475
Then I'll go back in there
and personally knock some sense into him!

215
00:14:06,725 --> 00:14:08,894
- That won't be necessary.
- Oh.

216
00:14:10,479 --> 00:14:14,232
I figured at least looking like a soldier
might bring back some more memories.

217
00:14:14,316 --> 00:14:16,485
Until I recover my equipment, anyway.

218
00:14:16,818 --> 00:14:18,195
I overheard you guys talking.

219
00:14:18,779 --> 00:14:20,781
I think I know where my armor is.

220
00:14:20,864 --> 00:14:22,240
Let's go check out the diner.

221
00:14:31,958 --> 00:14:34,336
Step it up, soldiers! This isn't a party.

222
00:14:34,628 --> 00:14:36,296
We do not have all night.

223
00:14:39,674 --> 00:14:41,218
Looking for this?

224
00:14:46,306 --> 00:14:48,433
My uniform. My equipment!

225
00:14:50,018 --> 00:14:52,813
All this time, you knew who I was
and didn't tell me?

226
00:14:53,271 --> 00:14:56,900
-Why?
-I don't care who you were.

227
00:14:57,192 --> 00:14:58,819
You are dishwasher now!

228
00:14:59,236 --> 00:15:02,739
And you owe me
for saving you from your crash!

229
00:15:03,365 --> 00:15:05,951
Your life is mine, Gregor.

230
00:15:06,034 --> 00:15:08,995
You didn't save me.
You turned me into a slave!

231
00:15:09,621 --> 00:15:12,040
I've worked in this dump,
taken orders from you,

232
00:15:12,124 --> 00:15:13,875
when I could have been fighting
for the Republic!

233
00:15:14,167 --> 00:15:15,252
I want my life back!

234
00:15:16,128 --> 00:15:17,963
You want your freedom, Gregor?

235
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:20,090
Take your gun from me.

236
00:15:20,382 --> 00:15:22,134
Show me you are a soldier.

237
00:15:24,094 --> 00:15:27,305
You see? You are no soldier.

238
00:15:27,556 --> 00:15:30,225
You are a dishwasher!

239
00:15:38,233 --> 00:15:40,068
Why, you no-good droids!

240
00:15:41,111 --> 00:15:42,696
Let go of me!

241
00:15:48,201 --> 00:15:51,288
Take your things, Gregor.
We're getting out of here.

242
00:15:54,207 --> 00:15:55,667
Don't leave, Gregor.

243
00:15:55,709 --> 00:15:57,878
It's a big galaxy out there.

244
00:15:58,170 --> 00:15:59,212
Bigger than you know!

245
00:15:59,713 --> 00:16:02,549
Stay here, where your life is simple.

246
00:16:02,883 --> 00:16:04,718
Simple isn't good enough anymore.

247
00:16:05,385 --> 00:16:06,678
Not for this clone.

248
00:16:07,220 --> 00:16:10,182
Ha! You will never get off Abafar.

249
00:16:10,557 --> 00:16:13,727
You and your little Republic friends.

250
00:16:13,977 --> 00:16:16,563
Not after your Jedi cruiser blows up!

251
00:16:17,397 --> 00:16:19,191
What are you talking about?

252
00:16:19,566 --> 00:16:22,569
Why do you think the Separatists
bother coming here?

253
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:27,073
They are mining our Rhydonium
to load on the shuttle

254
00:16:27,157 --> 00:16:28,867
and destroy your ride home!

255
00:16:31,536 --> 00:16:35,582
You will see, you will all be stuck here,

256
00:16:35,832 --> 00:16:39,085
begging Borkus for a job
in his diner!

257
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:03,193
Okay, let's see what we're up against.

258
00:17:03,276 --> 00:17:04,319
Gregor?

259
00:17:10,325 --> 00:17:11,701
Wait. There!

260
00:17:12,077 --> 00:17:13,328
There's a cruiser up there.

261
00:17:14,496 --> 00:17:15,914
And that shuttle. I think...

262
00:17:15,997 --> 00:17:17,165
Yes.

263
00:17:17,499 --> 00:17:19,793
It's being loaded up
with Rhydonium canisters.

264
00:17:22,462 --> 00:17:26,716
Ah, I guess Mr. Borkus was actually
telling the truth, for once.

265
00:17:27,092 --> 00:17:29,052
What exactly is Rhydonium?

266
00:17:29,344 --> 00:17:32,430
It's a fuel,
mostly been mined out on Abafar.

267
00:17:33,014 --> 00:17:34,349
It's volatile and dangerous.

268
00:17:36,935 --> 00:17:39,187
Yes, we do have a new mission.

269
00:17:39,646 --> 00:17:42,899
Stop the Separatists
from blowing up that cruiser.

270
00:17:43,650 --> 00:17:46,653
I'll cover you and clear the way, Colonel.
You all head straight to the shuttle.

271
00:17:46,820 --> 00:17:48,530
I'll take care of those clankers.

272
00:17:48,655 --> 00:17:50,824
Mmm, sounds like a good plan.

273
00:17:51,324 --> 00:17:53,660
You soldiers ready to get dangerous?

274
00:17:58,248 --> 00:17:59,332
I'll meet you at the shuttle, sir.

275
00:18:00,834 --> 00:18:02,127
Let's roll.

276
00:18:09,718 --> 00:18:10,802
Hey!

277
00:18:13,221 --> 00:18:15,682
You need authorization to enter this area.

278
00:18:19,894 --> 00:18:21,062
Get them!

279
00:18:38,913 --> 00:18:40,290
Good job, Gregor!

280
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,298
Look! He's up there!

281
00:18:57,474 --> 00:18:59,768
Just keep moving ! It is all under control!

282
00:19:07,317 --> 00:19:09,944
I'm beginning to remember
how much I hate these guys.

283
00:19:14,616 --> 00:19:16,743
Hey, I don't recognize those astromechs.

284
00:19:16,826 --> 00:19:17,869
Blast them!

285
00:19:18,995 --> 00:19:20,080
They are on to us!

286
00:19:23,625 --> 00:19:25,210
Colonel ! Can you hear me?

287
00:19:25,710 --> 00:19:28,088
-Save yourselves!
-Okay!

288
00:19:28,296 --> 00:19:29,464
Whoa!

289
00:19:30,423 --> 00:19:31,675
Whoa.

290
00:19:42,894 --> 00:19:44,229
Did everybody make it?

291
00:19:45,397 --> 00:19:47,691
No, Beezee and the Colonel
are still out there.

292
00:19:48,024 --> 00:19:49,275
Get the shuttle ready to roll.

293
00:19:58,451 --> 00:19:59,577
Colonel ! You all right?

294
00:19:59,786 --> 00:20:02,163
I'll never make it back alive.

295
00:20:02,330 --> 00:20:05,041
Yes, you will, sir!
This is what I was born to do.

296
00:20:05,125 --> 00:20:07,210
Now go, before it's too late!

297
00:20:29,858 --> 00:20:31,651
It's been an honor
serving with you, Colonel.

298
00:20:34,654 --> 00:20:38,032
Artoo's right.
We can swing back around and pick you up.

299
00:20:38,408 --> 00:20:39,868
Don't worry about me!

300
00:20:40,744 --> 00:20:42,662
You made me remember who I am!

301
00:20:42,704 --> 00:20:44,497
<i>I'll make my way home. I promise!</i>

302
00:20:44,706 --> 00:20:45,749
Now go!

303
00:20:50,044 --> 00:20:51,087
Where is Gregor?

304
00:20:51,212 --> 00:20:52,589
<i>Where is Gregor?</i>

305
00:20:53,339 --> 00:20:55,717
He's doing what a soldier does,

306
00:20:55,884 --> 00:20:59,179
sacrificing himself for the lives of others.

307
00:21:22,702 --> 00:21:25,205
You will be remembered, Captain Gregor.

308
00:21:26,122 --> 00:21:29,709
We will take your heroic story
back to the Republic,

309
00:21:30,043 --> 00:21:32,462
and we will watch for your return.

310
00:21:34,613 --> 00:21:39,613
http://hiqve.com/

